displayProperties.description: "You know, I used to think if it's marked a dead zone, it's my kind of place. Vanguard cured me of that, but I left plenty behind there back in the day. Third-floor balcony, above the alley.  Loved that spot…. Hope the Fallen haven't got to it." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "You do much driving? Me neither. But I used to spend nights hiding out near this truck just teetering on a ledge, just waiting for the day some dumb Dreg would send it over the ledge. That day never came." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So I took off edging the cliff, Golden Gun down to one shot. Left a lot behind cliffside. Bad day." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So after a full day of pulling loot out of the Fallen's hands, I thought I would just cool my engines down by that old river, but as soon as I cached it all up down there, a Servitor shows up." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I used to have this old lookout. Scoped out my first FWC bunker there. Just like the Cabal to plop that eyesore of a base right on top of a piece of dark age nostalgia. Do me a favor, if you make it up there: snipe a few rhinos for me." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I tell you what. You get to work cleaning out the angry spider-pirates and space-rhinos, and I give you the deed to this little cabin I won from Ren. With a little work, could become a nice little getaway." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "OK, all I can give you to go on in this one is… it's high up. So… look up, I guess? Don't look at me like that, I'm doing my best.” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I've been all around this system, seen all sorts of transports, but nothing with the resiliency of this old Golden Age rustbucket I found in the EDZ. Used it as a grab-and-go spot for years." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "This place is full of old containers. Don't bother raiding them all—I already did. They're all filled with shoes. Mountains of Golden Age footwear, and not a thing in my size." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So once you get up there, don't be afraid to strut it on the catwalk. We both know the importance of looking good." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: “Good news: I remember exactly where one of my old EDZ caches is. Bad news: those parts are Taken territory now. So I guess the question is: how bad d'you want it?”
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Stashed plenty of loot up at the old mill in the EDZ. To scare the Dregs off, I'd throw on some old Festival of the Lost masks and make 'em think the place was haunted." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "They thought they had me dead-to-sights… backing me down this cliff. But I could see some fellow Hunters sparrowing in from the highway. Classic. So I sparked up a little Golden Gun and bought my guys some time.  I know I dropped something good in that one." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "New lead from Hawthorne. Not really much to go on, something about a fan. I know I must have a lot of them, so if you see one down in the EDZ, maybe ask them?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Listen, I feel bad making you go after my stuff, so last night I snuck down to the EDZ. Sh-sh-sh, don't tell Zavala! Anyway, I got the cache, then got a tiny bit turned around and ended up in a Cabal base. You know how that is. The dogs and all. Had to stash the goods quickly and get out. So… can you go get it?” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: EDZ Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I always used Titan as a rest stop before hitting the Reef. Something about those waves. This one's right under your nose. And your feet." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "OK, I actually made a sketch to remind me of this one. And it looks like I put it… near some kind of windmill. Or fan. Or something." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Getting pings on another one somewhere high up in one of those towers. From what I hear, the Fallen are using those towers as some kind of junkyard. Could be like a needle in a haystack. Good luck.” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I take it you like to jump, right? I see the way you jump all around the Tower. Guardians these days—no respect for gravity." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Titan who gave me the lead said he stood there watching their spawning crud just repel off my cache… too scared to touch it. You aren't scared of a little Hive fungus are you?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So I chased the gang of Awoken thieves up to the Arcology. That bridge didn't look too stable, and I'm not into methane baths, so I stashed what I had and picked up their trail inside." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "What idiot crashed the tank into the wall? It definitely, one hundred percent, absolutely wasn't me. You believe me, right?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "This one is in some kind of wall. What was it with the Golden Age that they built walls around everything?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Mapping these pings to the latest from Sloane, looks like you'll be tearing through some kind of ceiling garden. Good luck with that.” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So this cache… all I remember is it's in a very… blue room. You'll know it when you see it." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "You know what I used to love about my rest stops on Titan? Walking into the Arcology and thinking about it in its heyday. But then you get to thinking of how much we actually lost, and now the Hive just spawning everywhere… and the will to fight boils right back up." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "We Exo must've had it made back in the Golden Age. Just my presence alone seems to bypass any active security measures in the Arcologies." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "And just to amuse myself I would find natural x's in any environment and stash something somewhere beneath them, just to be able to say those words to myself… 'X marks the spot.'”
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Those Fallen on Titan. I've been after them for years. They ransacked an old trove I kept in the Sink on Venus, then went completely dark. Getting pings on one, but everyone who's been after it gets lost in the dark way down below." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Reef Awoken are weird like that. She assured me it was a gold mine, so I went exploring. Check near some kind of generator machine thing, there should be one I haven't hit in years." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Titan Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Of course, I didn't go charging into Nessus without a plan. I made sure I had caches everywhere. Started with the first dead Vex construct I found." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "One point, I thought I'd broken free, so I made a break for a path through a tangle of roots. Caught sight of the cache and then bam, I was back in the loop again." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "It was like I was being called closer, like something wanted my help. Then I get to this tower with a triangular doorway and go through. That's when it got really weird." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I don't know what they call it. The eyeball thing. Under that. You'll know it when you see it." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So down I went. I thought maybe the deeper it got, the better access I would have to their core Mind or Nexus points. I do read Ikora's Vex reports. Sometimes. Anyway, found nothing but roots." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So this cache… I don't know. It seemed like a good idea at the time. How do you feel about climbing trees?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I was just doing what Failsafe said. I mean, she seems reliable, half the time. So I entered this cave and set up my little fallback point, took a few steps in, and bam, the battle began." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I guess I was afraid that Mind juice would somehow seize control of my weapons or something. That stuff isn't some kind of luxurious milk bath, trust me." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Good news: I left myself a reminder note for this cache! Bad news: the note says ‘Whatever you do, under any circumstances, do not look down.' That's enough to go on, right?”
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I wonder if the Vex even realize I hide stuff between the gaps in their block networks. Hmmm. Maybe that's how they know so much about me." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So there I was, two choices: I could've tried climbing the red ivy, or just jump. What do you think I did?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I had no choice. Once I saw the floating rocks, there was no way I was going to weigh myself down with extra gear. I was Lightless after all, remember?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I should've realized something was up when the Vex were letting me move through portals so freely. And I usually have a good nose for traps. Maybe you'll have better luck?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I felt bad using their wreckage to hide my stuff, but Failsafe said it was cool. And she says she's been keeping the Vex from converting the Exodus Black, so I figured it would be safe.” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Thought I'd escaped, but you know how the Vex are. I got as far as this energy shield, thinking it was a way out. Dead end. So I dropped what I had there and tried to shoot through. Bam! Right back into the loop.”
displayProperties.name: Nessus Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "The lead I got from Asher was some Psion was seen making off with this one somewhere in the Echo Mesa. He mumbled something about it being on top of some Cabal checkpoint, before it—well—fell into a pit of Taken. And we all know how that turns out." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Damn Rhinos. Made off with everything from my lockers when they ransacked the Tower. This one here, they dragged to Io and apparently left it behind. Last ping I got came from their abandoned base on the Echo Mesa." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Asher called me to rant about a Taken Blight destroying a research wing of the Cabal base, and I'm like, why are you telling me? We're not friends; and then he mentions seeing one of my caches in the debris. Survived a Taken Blight. Not a bad design, if I do say so myself." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Bear with me. I have this memory on Io where I was just sniping Vex from a ledge. Then the sky went dark, and man, I can't remember anything but pain and running and calling for an evac. I know I left something behind on that one." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So word is one of the Cabal's drill engineers found another one of my caches. I don't know if I did such a good job sealing it or if those dumb rhino fingers are too fat to pry it open. Anyway, it's been spotted in some hole near that drill site. I guess Ghaul called them back before they could get into it." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "OK, so, Albios's memorial service was on Io. Sacred to Warlocks, blah blah blah. Don't get me wrong, I liked Al—but the service ran a bit long. Ended up betting Banshee I could make a few hairy jumps high up on the Mesa. Broke both my legs, but I did it. I forget what Banshee gave me, but I know I left it in a cache up there somewhere.” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "OK, another live cache report here… Gotta give the Cabal credit. They're great at digging tunnels. Then again, so are worms… and snakes… and woodchucks… and crabs... and ants… ugh, I hate ants." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "You ever talk to Banshee much? He's got this saying: Sometime the deeper you go, the less you'll ever understand. The Cabal are kind of like that. Why they feel the need to drag my stuff into their damn Io base… beyond me." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Gotta love the views on Io. I remember watching Jupiter float over the horizon, all big and stormy. I left a cache up there, and… fell asleep. Next thing I know, my Ghost's reviving me at the base of the cliff. Guess I roll around in my sleep.” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Do me a favor and just look into that Pyramidion thing, would you?  If the Vex are studying the best of humanity, you know they've got stuff on me in there.” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "When I was caught in that Vex Teleporter, I would end up in weird places. Once or twice, I swear it was Io and saw one of my own caches on top one of those tall, pointy Vex things. That's all I got for you. That ‘porter was not a fun time!” —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Funny thing, I know I've been to Io, but all the details are pretty hazy. Guess I'm getting old.  I have this memory of a battle on a bridge. Vex everywhere. After crossing a bridge, we took cover to the right, and then, well, it gets fuzzy from there. Maybe worth checking out?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "You know Eris Morn, right? Creepy three-eyed old Hunter, too much foundation? Doesn't matter. She comes in and asks me how Io was and I say, wrong Vanguard, ask Ikora; and she's like, I was hoping that cache by the bones marked your grave; and I'm like, I'm an Exo, I left my bones behind a long time ago; and she goes, exactly. You get anything from that?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Have you ever had a dream you're in this cave full of mist and you see this amazing cache, but every time you reach to open it, a new layer of mists blocks your path? No? Am I the only one who has this dream?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I got word on another cache in the Echo Mesa. Some of Asher's 'assistants' chased a Legionary out of the Cabal Base but lost him in a little cave nearby. Must've left it there, since the rhino came out empty handed. That's when the assistants got him. Good thing, 'cause I'd rather it go to you." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Io Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Was actually trying to bring the Lighthouse some supplies. You know, since Almighty ate half the planet. But Vance wouldn't let me in! Couldn't find another way in, so I just left the stash near the door… near-ish." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I have this feeling the Followers don't go outside much. Shame, too. If it was me, I'd be sunning myself on that patio thing they got going out there. Top-notch real estate." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "So it's like a big stone ball, but it's got a fountain of radio-whatever on it. Don't look at me like that. I'm literally describing the topography." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I was trying to find a back door to the Infinite Forest. First place I looked? The actual back of the Forest door. No Vex doomsday machine, but I found a good spot for a stash." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Good news: I left myself a note for this one. Bad news: the note just says 'live on the edge.' So… there you go." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Got it in my head to scale that canyon on Mercury, the one so deep you can't see the bottom. Left a stash on a ledge near the top. Shouldn't have to go too far to find it." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Is it just me, or does the Lighthouse have a lot of broken doors? Well, if no one's using them as doors, I might as well use them as stash markers." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Vance still won't let me in the Lighthouse! Can you believe it? Tried to hack that stupid door of his. Almost got it, too. Left some supplies behind for the next try." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "They just kept warping in out of nowhere. I was handling it, you know, until—you get it. Anyway, I wasn't hiding behind the waterfall. Just regrouping." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Mercury Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Y'know, I'd tell you to look for the power generator, but I'll be honest—all this computer-y stuff? Looks the same to me. This one was pretty… small. I guess we all look pretty small standing next to Rasputin, though." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "I'm not an engineer, but I'd bet half my stash on the fact that no one has any idea what any of this stuff actually does. I think these guys just like how all these nooks and hidey-holes look." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Have you ever actually crawled through an air duct? Not nearly as easy as it looks. I mean, I'm good at it, but I'm…well, me. All I'm saying is the trick is in angling your shoulders. And not having a big lunch." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Let me tell you the real truth about machines—they're a lot more like people than you'd think. Some are fine, some are just jerks. Rasputin? Totally right-brained. I think." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Have you ever heard of a Warsat doing something OTHER than crashing? Don't get me wrong, I appreciate the service of our Warsats, but at a certain point you have to ask: what do they do?" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Wherever it is, you're gonna want to bring a coat, 'cause it sounds real cold. My horn was frozen like a popsicle, if you could imagine. When you find it, you're in for a splendid view. But yeah, bring a coat." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Hiding treasure is an art. And there are a lot of different kinds of art, right? This would be an art piece that's an ironic metacommentary about art, if that makes sense. Yeah, that totally doesn't make sense." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Bray's an interesting place. I have a complicated relationship with it, given my past and all. But I've gotta admit, they've built some dang impressive stuff for the whole system. The Golden Age must have been a wild time to be alive." —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map

displayProperties.description: "Snow. It's cold, it's wet, and it's generally pretty great to throw at people. But you know what else it's good for? Hiding things. I wonder where I can get some white paint around here…" —Cayde-6
displayProperties.name: Hellas Basin Treasure Map
